item.title: Java import help
item.dc:creator: @zyle1992 Zymus
item.description:
@zyle1992 wrote:

[quote=“Blood zeus, post:3, topic:454861”]class80.java:6: error: package netscape does not exist import netscape.javascript.JSObject;
Oh, so if I’m getting this error, it’s something to do with a core java file aswell, since this also doesn’t have a directory anywhere?[/quote]

No. I’m guessing that you’re trying to compile a (relatively) new client. Basically, when you get an error like that, it means that the package is not in the current classpath.
